 It said, they were all brought to this one central location

00:07:32.360 --> 00:07:35.160
 in Moscow, and they were kind of put the cadaver

00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:39.360
 on a tilt table, and drain the blood, and weirdly,

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:42.800
 and this was carried on by Jack Kovorkian in the US

00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:44.120
 and some other people in the US saying,

00:07:44.120 --> 00:07:45.520
 like, why are we wasting this?

00:07:45.520 --> 00:07:47.920
 This is perfectly good blood.

00:07:47.920 --> 00:07:51.440
 And the weird thing is if somebody had died suddenly,

00:07:51.440 --> 00:07:53.760
 the blood wouldn't coagulate in the same way.

00:07:53.760 --> 00:07:55.320
 It was actually more useful blood.

00:07:55.320 --> 00:07:56.880
 And I didn't include this in my book.

