00:10:01.960 --> 00:10:03.520
 Do you remember telling us what happens

00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:06.600
 with carbonated water in transit?

00:10:06.600 --> 00:10:09.640
 - It's not my personal theory,

00:10:09.640 --> 00:10:11.960
 but I have been perpetuating it, absolutely.

00:10:11.960 --> 00:10:16.240
 Mary, there's an idea that sparkling water

00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:20.200
 when it's being transferred in large containerships

00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:21.800
 across from country to country,

00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:24.800
 that the bubbles are removed from the water,

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:26.680
 so as to not lose the fizz in transit.

00:10:26.680 --> 00:10:28.200
 And then at the other port,

00:10:28.200 --> 00:10:30.000
 when it's reached its destination,

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:34.280
 the same bubbles are replaced into the water itself.

00:10:34.280 --> 00:10:37.080
 - They store the bubbles?

00:10:37.080 --> 00:10:38.920
 - Well, the bubbles have the same bubbles.

00:10:38.920 --> 00:10:40.240
 They fly, obviously,

00:10:40.240 --> 00:10:42.680
 'cause they're a lot lighter to transport.

00:10:42.680 --> 00:10:43.520
 - Yes.

00:10:43.520 --> 00:10:44.360
 - Yeah.

00:10:44.360 --> 00:10:46.000
 - Is there a reason you bring this up?

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:48.360
 - Yeah, well, I hate to bring Dan.

00:10:48.360 --> 00:10:51.360
 - Which is reason enough in itself.

00:10:51.360 --> 00:10:55.040
 But I didn't realize there is sort of a slight analogy

00:10:55.040 --> 00:10:56.400
 in what happens when you donate blood.

00:10:56.400 --> 00:10:59.200
 So I just had no idea what happened when you donate blood.

00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:00.040
 I haven't done it before.

00:11:00.040 --> 00:11:01.120
 I think I might do it off the back of this.

00:11:01.120 --> 00:11:03.080
 It sounds like it's a very, very worthwhile thing to do.

00:11:03.080 --> 00:11:04.480
 But when you donate it,

00:11:04.480 --> 00:11:08.720
 it's immediately split up into separate components.

00:11:08.720 --> 00:11:13.040
 So they put it in a centrifuge and spin it,

00:11:13.040 --> 00:11:14.200
 and you know, in a centrifuge,

00:11:14.200 --> 00:11:17.040
 it spins incredibly fast and different components

00:11:17.040 --> 00:11:20.320
 spin out to different sort of areas in the centrifuge.

00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:21.480
